 through your journey as a knight. Whether it be improving your personal martial skills, or increasing your ability to lead bigger retinues, investing in your knight will allow you greater power and ability to conquer other lands.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2782030/extras/Screenshot_2025-01-07_171557.png?t=1737158409\" /></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">You'll need soldiers if you want to destroy anything larger than a bandit group. Levy from your peasant population a basic army, though at the cost of not being able to put them to work, and lead them in battle against enemy forces. Different units are strong or weak against varying enemy types, so choose your army well. With more development and resources, you may even recruit professional soldiers that are superior to the levies, and don't take away from the labor pool, although their cost is higher than a simple peasant recruit.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2782030/extras/Screenshot_2025-01-07_171753.png?t=1737158409\" /></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Sometimes, or rather all the time, it's more fun to play with friends. Bring your fellow knights into your game and conquer the lands together through multiplayer.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p>","developers":["ES Galore"],"genres":[{"description":"Action","id":"1"},{"description":"Casual","id":"4"},{"description":"Indie","id":"23"},{"description":"RPG","id":"3"},{"description":"Strategy","id":"2"},{"description":"Early Access","id":"70"}],"header_image":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2782030/header.jpg?t=1737158409","is_free":false,"linux_requirements":[],"mac_requirements":[],"movies":[{"highlight":true,"id":257083415,"mp4"